snippet: Amid music institutions’ bonanza of composer anniversaries, Debussy’s 150th birthday is slipping by in relative silence — partly, perhaps, because he’s relatively hard to label.
abstract: Debussy’s 150th birthday is slipping by relatively unacknowledged amid music institutions’ bonanza of composer anniversaries, perhaps, because he’s relatively hard to label; Debussy was a contrary sort, an artist who knew what he did not like but not always where he belonged, which may explain his being overlooked.
lead_paragraph: Amid music institutions’ bonanza of composer anniversaries, Debussy’s 150th birthday is slipping by in relative silence — partly, perhaps, because he’s relatively hard to label.

headline.main: Debussy at 150: The Impressions Still Deceive
headline.print_headline: Debussy at 150: The Impressions Still Deceive
